\subsection{Proof that \versecalc{} Is Skew Confluent}


Proof sketch:

First prove that the modified $\runi$ is skew confluent. (In doing so we will define $\runi_{\leqomegavc}^{\leftarrow}$.)

Then use existing proofs to demonstrate that $\rapp \cup \rcon \cup \rgc \cup \rspc$ is confluent.
Because they are also monotonic, they are therefore skew confluent, and $(\rapp \cup \rcon \cup \rgc \cup \rspc) _{\leqomegavc}^{\leftarrow}$ is trivial.

Prove that $\rapp \cup \rcon \cup \rgc \cup \rspc$ commutes with $\runi_{\leqomegavc}^{\leftarrow}$.

Then apply \cref {lem:skew-union} to show that $\runi \cup (\rapp \cup \rcon \cup \rgc \cup \rspc)$ is skew confluent.
